                <note rend="inline" type="source">724.3415/1248: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Morgan</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-06-30T17:00:00-04:00"
                            >June 30, 1931—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>49. Your 42, June 29, 4 p.m. This Government and the neutral Governments are
                    counseling moderation on the part of both Bolivia and Paraguay and expressing
                    the hope that diplomatic relations will not be broken and that this incident
                    will be settled and will not be permitted to develop in such a way as to
                    endanger the holding of the conference suggested in the neutral Governments’
                    notes of June 25<note n="74" xml:id="d581fn74">See telegrams of June 22, 7 p.m.,
                        to the Chargé in Bolivia (No. 23) and the Chargé in Paraguay (No. 20), <ref
                            target="#pg_725">pp. 725</ref> and <ref target="#pg_727"
                        >727</ref>.</note> for a settlement of the vital Chaco question. Any support
                    in this sense by the Brazilian Government will be most welcome.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Castle</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
